Fort Carson soldier who disappeared Monday night found alive The soldier was found, alive and in good condition, after a 24-hour search.
A Fort Carson soldier, missing since Monday night, has been found alive and in good condition after a 24-hour search, the U.S. Army announced on Wednesday.
"The Soldier has displayed physical and mental toughness as a Soldier and persevered through a challenging situation.
I want to extend my deepest appreciation to all of the Soldiers of Fort Carson, along with the Colorado Springs community, for their diligent work while searching for and bringing our Soldier home."
Fort Carson army base in Colorado in a 2015, image from Google maps.